RIYADH: Khazenly, an Egypt-based warehousing platform, raised $2.5 million in a seed funding round co-led by venture capital firms Arzan Venture Capital and Shorooq Partners. The company provides solutions to support merchants with their business and logistics operations, MAGNiTT reported. “Our simplified, technology-fueled platform, high-caliber experienced team, and network of market-leading partners help merchants grow and scale,” Mohamed Younes, co-founder and chief executive officer, said in a statement. Founded in 2021, Khazenly will use its acquired funds to grow its product portfolio as well as empower current products to further support merchants.